File: Federations had petitioned government about the possibility of making a return during lockdown. JOHANNESBURG - Sport has been thrown a lifeline. Federations had petitioned government about the possibility of making a return during lockdown. That has now been confirmed, although specifics remain unclear for now. "Public training, fitness and recreational facilities remain closed except those conducting non-contact sports matches without spectators," Cogta Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma said. READ: Spit, sweat and shaking on it: three sports habits that could change after coronavirus Dlamini-Zuma said health protocols and social distancing must be strictly observed, including wearing of masks. "We will lift the curfew and allow more time for exercise, walking and cycling," she said. "However, this is permitted as long as this is not done in organised groups." The country will move to Level 3 of the lockdown on 1 June. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.